						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall, central shrine, Āmravanēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 9 = 980 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records a gift of 25 <hi rend="italic">kāśu</hi> for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple of Ādittēsvaram-uḍaiya-Bhaṭṭārakar at Kūrūr in Tirunaraiyūr-nāḍu by one Astra-Śiva. He entrusted the money with the <hi rend="italic">tiruvuṇṇāḻigai-pperumakkaḷ</hi> of the temple for carrying out the benefaction.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. XIX No. 232.</p>						

						</summary>
